messages.message:
I've seen a couple of unexpected but intermittent errors on Cypress tests in the past couple of runs -
• In aihub-refinement the full value wasn't extracted https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/12472/overview/6cea1f17-214c-407c-a3d2-0409b3c1e62b?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1
• In aihub-validation-library a case that should have been a PASS was a FAIL https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/12475/overview/585cfdae-2390-40dc-bcc2-21d8f5acc674?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1 (I saw this on one of Xindi's runs too)
I know CJ is out, maybe cc @Arjun
i saw the aihub-validation-library failure in some of my recent CI runs as well, but it’s a flaky failure, so it passed when i reran CI
i just changed aihub-refinement to actually run extraction, instead of using a mocked extraction job, so let me take a look
I had my eyes on the runs, but didn’t see a pattern. But good to know!
the model isn’t returning the entire expected value - it’s returning `5701 GOLDEN HILLS DRIVE` instead of `5701 GOLDEN HILLS DRIVE MINNEAPOLIS, MN 55416-1297`

when i ran `aihub-refinement`, it succeeded twice, but now that i’m looking at the extraction result, the field confidence is pretty low (around 50%)

i tweaked the field name, and the field confidence is a lot higher (around 80%), so we can try that to see if it works more consistently
i got the same failure on my PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/60377), so i pushed the field name change there to see if CI passes
the aihub-validation-library flaky failures pre-date my changes, so they’re flaky for a different reason

ah i remember now, arjun has previously mentioned that `aihub-validation-library` is flaky because `resetBuildProjectData` is sometimes flaky

`aihub-validation-library` uses `resetBuildProjectData` to set up the schema in the project and save some hard-coded extraction values (see here (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/master/webserver/shared/src/js/webpacked/apps/src/aihub/__e2e__/BuildApp/aihub-validation-library.spec.ts#L50-L75))

however, sometimes this hard-coding doesn’t work, and we still trigger extraction (see screenshot of `POST extraction` being called in Jessica’s CI run)

i diffed the hard-coded extracted values with the results of the unexpected `POST extraction` call and found some discrepancies that could trigger the extraction call - i’m testing my changes for resolving these discrepancies rn
again, after testing locally, i pushed the same fix to my existing PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/60377), so we’ll see if CI passes
